      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "s = input()\nlength = int(input())\npad = input()\n\npadding_needed = length - len(s)\n\n# Repeat pad as much as needed and cut last one if necessary\nfull_padding = (pad * ((padding_needed // len(pad)) + 1))[:padding_needed]\n\n# Left padding\nresult = full_padding + s\nprint(result)",
      "statement": "Given a string [[s]], a positive integer [[length]], and a string [[pad]], print [[s]] as a string of the given length, padding it on the left with the string [[pad]] (if necessary) to reach the required length. The padding is formed by adding [[pad]] as many times as necessary and then truncating it from the right (if necessary) to fit exactly.",
